Vintage illustration of an intricate mechanical postal system with brass tubes, gears, and pneumatic capsules connecting ornate Victorian-era document cabinets. Multiple glass cylinders contain rolled parchments traveling along curved copper pipes that branch and merge like a transit map. At the center, an elaborate sorting mechanism with spinning wheels and clockwork components directs capsules to different destinations. The scene has warm sepia tones with touches of deep burgundy and aged gold, reminiscent of 19th-century technical drawings and steampunk aesthetics. Soft ambient lighting creates depth and highlights the polished metal surfaces. The composition suggests interconnectedness and the elegant complexity of routing information between different systems.
